      "message": "is there an intention to make this API usable in other applications?\nI think if that\u0027s the goal then we should accept a build in this request (as opposed to its commit and its builder), because we are retrieve a blamelist of a build, not a commit+builder.\n\nbut I am not sure that should be the goal. To me, this service and its methods are examples of \"UI-specific RPC\". From that perspective, having gitiles commit and builder here makes sense. \n\nanother reason not to advertise this API to others is that we might want to add more stuff here that is specific to our page, but makes no sense to others.\n\nso IMO instead we should put a loud warning that nobody should use this private API.",
